        "timestamp": "2018-05-03 20:39:27.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nKevin, may be you can help Joseph, here the comment is the polluting of this configuration files in many places.   There should be only one logback.xml per \"process\", since integrity-audit and integrity-monitor are just libraries.   Logging should piggyback into existing processes logback.xml and be redirected to the appropriate log, debug, audit, error, etc ..   The current set up causes logging structures using eelf with directory names such as integrity-monitor, etc ..   The question is can these files be deleted all together?",
        "patchset_number": 1
